org.glassfish.hk2.tests.api

Class ComplexHierarchy

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.glassfish.hk2.tests.api.ParameterizedObject
      • org.glassfish.hk2.tests.api.MarkerInterfaceImpl
        • org.glassfish.hk2.tests.api.MarkerInterface2Impl
          • org.glassfish.hk2.tests.api.ComplexHierarchy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MarkerInterface, MarkerInterface2, ParameterizedInterface<String>

    @UseProxy(value=false)
public class ComplexHierarchy
extends MarkerInterface2Impl
    This guy extends a class that is not a contract but implements an interface which is a contract. That subclass also extends a class that IS a contract and who implements an interface that is NOT a contract. This then in turn extends a parameterized object that is NOT a contract while the parameterized interface it implements IS a contract Thus the generated contracts for this object should be:
    1. ComplexHierarch
    2. MarkerInterfaceImpl
    3. MarkerInterface2
    4. ParameterizedInterface
